<h1>Courses for the 98-99 Academic Year</h1><p><br>

<h2>Math Courses:</h2>
At present, the following courses will definitely be offered.

<ul>
<li><b> Fall 1998</b>:
<ul>
<li><b>Math for Human Ecologists</b>. <i>Instructor:  Don Cass</i>. 
<li><b>College Algebra I</b>. <i>Instructor:  Bo Greene</i>.
</ul> 
<li> <b> Winter 1999</b>
<ul>
<li> <b> Calculus I</b>. <i>Instructor:  <a
href="http://hornacek.coa.edu/dave/">Dave Feldman</a></i>.
</ul>
<li> <b> Spring 1999</b>
<ul>
<li> <b> Calculus II</b>. <i>Instructor:  <a
href="http://hornacek.coa.edu/dave/">Dave Feldman</a></i>.
</ul>
</ul>
<p><br>

<h3>Other Math Possibilities:</h3><p>

<ul>

<li>I may coordinate <b>Introduction to Scientific
Computing</b> as an independent study this fall.  (The language will
be c++, no experience necessary.)  If you have some
interest in taking this, contact me (<a
href="mailto:dave@hornacek.coa.edu">dave@hornacek.coa.edu</a>) as soon
as possible.

<li>Also, I (Dave) will be teaching an <b>as yet undecided course</b>
in the spring.  It is likely that this will be a "science and society"
sort of course that will not be heavily quantitative and will not
satisfy the quantitative reasoning requirement.  

<li>It is quite likely, although still not definite, that Bo Greene
will teach <b>College Algebra II</b> this winter, a continuation of
the Algebra courses she taught last Spring and will be teaching again
this Fall.

<li>There is a very slight chance that Sean Todd will teach
<b>Probability and Statistics</b> course later this year.  If
statistics is not offered this year, it will definitely be offered in
99-00. 

<li>I might be willing to teach a tutorial in an advanced area of math
or physics.  Interested students should contact me.
</ul>



<h3>Other Courses with a Quantitative Emphasis</h3>

<ul>
<li><b> Fall 1998</b>:
<ul>
<li><b>Introduction to Chemistry I</b>. <i>Instructor:  Don Cass</i>. 
<li><b>Physics I</b>. <i>Instructor:  <a
href="http://hornacek.coa.edu/dave">Dave Feldman</a></i>.
</ul> 
<li> <b> Winter 1999</b>
<ul>
<li><b>Introduction to Chemistry II</b>. <i>Instructor:  Don
Cass</i>. 
<li> <b> Physics II</b>. <i>Instructor:  <a
href="http://hornacek.coa.edu/dave/">Dave Feldman</a></i>.
<li><b>Biomechanics</b>. <i>Instructor: Helen Hess</i>.
</ul>
<li> <b> Spring 1999</b>
<ul>
<li> <b> Calculus II</b>. <i>Instructor:  <a
href="http://hornacek.coa.edu/dave/">Dave Feldman</a></i>.
</ul>
</ul>
<p>

Note: Intro to Chemistry I does <b>not</b> satisfy the quantitative
reasoning requirement.<p><br> 



